
[1]adversity

   ADVERS'ITY, n. An event, or series of events, which oppose success or
   desire; misfortune; calamity; affliction; distress; state of
   unhappiness.

   In the day of adversity, consider. Eccl. 7.

   Ye have rejected God, who saved you out of all you adversities. 1Sam.
   10.
